# ks-gen output exception

ks-gen is licensed under the GNU General Public License, version 3 or
later (GPL-3.0-or-later). The full text of the GPL is in `LICENSE`.

This file grants one additional permission under section 7 of the GPL.

## Additional permission

As a special exception, the Jinja2 template files in
`src/ks_gen/templates/`, and the shell glue and kickstart syntax they
emit into files produced by running `ks-gen`, do not by themselves
cause the resulting output files to be covered by the GNU General
Public License.

Files produced by an unmodified `ks-gen` — including but not limited
to `ks.cfg`, `tailoring.xml`, `exceptions.md`, and any installer ISO
built by `ks-gen iso` — remain entirely at the operator's discretion
as to licensing and distribution.

The operator-authored input (`host.yaml`) is operator-owned in any
case and is not affected by this license.

## Modified versions

This permission applies to outputs of unmodified ks-gen and to outputs
of modified ks-gen distributed under the same exception. A downstream
modifier may, at their option, remove this exception; outputs of such
a modified version would then be governed by the GPL without this
additional permission.

## Precedent

This exception mirrors the spirit of GNU Bison's parser-skeleton
exception and the GCC Runtime Library Exception — both grant downstream
users the freedom to license generator output without inheriting the
generator's copyleft, while keeping the generator itself copyleft.
